clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Temocapril is an ACE inhibitor primarily indicated in the treatment of hypertension and congestive heart failure diabetic nephropathy and improvement of prognosis for coronary artery diseases including acute myocardial infarction

contraindications.disease: In rats whether or male or female the LD50 values of temocapril were higher than 5000 mg kg
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Temocapril is a prodrug of its active metabolite and diacid form temocaprilat which contains a thiazepine ring Temocaprilat has slightly higher potency than enalaprilat in ACE inhibition isolated from rabbit lung ACE inhibitors exert their hemodynamic effect mainly by inhibiting the renin angiotensin system They also modulate sympathetic nervous system activity and increase prostaglandin synthesis They cause mainly vasodilation and mild natriuresis without affecting heart rate and contractility When compared with other Angiotensin converting Enzyme Inhibitors temocapril s advantages include a rapid onset of action and what research suggests is tighter vascular ACE binding than enalaprilat
